                            <comment id="13532175" author="fpj" created="Fri, 14 Dec 2012 09:08:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1, this feature would be great.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13546686" author="hustlmsp" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2013 08:03:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;a straightforward change to using guava cache to store its owned topics and track its accesses (publish a new message, deliver messages).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;release topic when a entry is evicted from the cache. one is based on size (the owned topic reached the limitation that a hub server is supposed to own), the other one is based on &apos;expireAfterAccess&apos;, if a topic is inactive for a duration, the topic would be evicted and released.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;expireAfterAccess&apos; is better than fixed time retention, so we don&apos;t release hot topics.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
